obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (44394)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_187918_1523270691223&sectionId=44394&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_187918_1523270691223
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Legal Practitioners Act,`
  line `1879; and shall come into force on the first day of January, 1880.`
  line
  line `Local extent.--This section and section 2 extend to the whole of India ^1`
  line `[except the State of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir*.].`
  line
  line `^2[The rest of this Act extends, in the first instance, only to the territories which,`
  line `immediately before the 1st November, 1956, were comprised in West Bengal, Uttar`
  line `Pradesh, Punjab, Bihar, Madhya Pradesh, Assam, Orissa and Delhi. But the State`
  line `Government of any State may, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line extend^3
  line `all or any of the provisions of the rest of this Act to the whole or any part of that`
  line `State to which such provisions do not extend.]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Sch., for "except Part B States".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for the former paragraph.`
  line
  line `3. Under this power, the Act has been extended, subject to certain omissions and so far only as it relates to judicial Courts, Civil`
  line `and Criminal, to the Madras Presidency, except the Scheduled Districts, from 1st April 1882, see Fort St. George Gazette,`
  line `1881, Pt. I, pp. 491 and 707. Ss. 3 and 4 of the Act have been extended to the Regulation Districts of the Bombay Presidency,`
  line `see Bombay Government Gazette 1885, Pt. I, p. 290; and ss. 13 [except clauses (a), (b), (c), (d) and (f) thereof), 34, 36 and 40`
  line `have been extended, to the whole of the Bombay Presidency (Bombay Gazette, 1904, Pt. p. 1635). Ch. I, s. 40, Sch. II, and so`
  line `much of Chs. III, V, VI and VII as relates to pleaders, have been extended to Coorg, see Mysore Gazette, 1879, Pt . I, p. 355; see`
  line `also Coorg District Gazette, 1891, Pt. 1, p. 140, for notification extending ss. 4, 5 and 38; Coorg District Gazette, 1899, Pt. I, P. 122,`
  line `for notification extending ss. 3, 13 and 36 as amended by Act 11 of 1896 so far as they relate to pleaders; and Coorg Gazette, 1935,`
  line `Pt. I, A. 2, for notification extending ss. 4 and 41. Ss. 4 and 41 have been extended to Ajmer-Merwara, see Gazette id India, 1927,`
  line `Pt, II-A P. 214.`
  line
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
