obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `[Repeal of enactments.] Rep. by the Repealing Act, 1938 (1 of 1938) s. 2 and`
  line Schedule.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (44396)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_187918_1523270691223&sectionId=44396&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_187918_1523270691223
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there be something repugnant in the`
  line `subject or context,`
  line
  line `"Judge" means the presiding judicial officer in every Civil and Criminal Court, by`
  line `whatever title he is designated;`
  line
  line `"subordinate Court" means all Courts subordinate to the High Court, including Courts`
  line `of Small Causes established under Act No. 9 of 1850^1or Act No. 11 of 1865^2;`
  line
  line `"revenue-office" includes all Courts (other than Civil Courts) trying suits under any Act for the`
  line `time being in force relating to landholders and their tenants or agents ;`
  line
  line `"legal practitioner" means an advocate, vakil or attorney of any High Court, a pleader mukhtar or`
  line `revenue-agent ;`
  line
  line `^3["tout" means a person--`
  line
  line `(a) who procures, in consideration of any remuneration moving from any legal`
  line `practitioner, the employment of the legal practitioner in any legal business; or who proposes`
  line `to any legal practitioner or to any person interested in any legal business to procure, in`
  line `consideration of any remuneration moving from either of them, the employment of the legal`
  line `practitioner in such business; or`
  line
  line `(b) who for the purposes of such procurement frequent the precincts of Civil or Criminal`
  line `Courts or of revenue-offices, or railway stations, landing stages, lodging places or other`
  line `places of public resort.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See now the Presidency Small Cause Courts Act, 1882 (15 of 1882).`
  line
  line `2. See now the Provincial Small Cause Courts Act, 1887 (9 of 1887).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 15 of 1926, s. 2, for the former definition.`
